This paper deals with object detection in high-resolution equirectangular panorama images, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) techniques. The proposed multi-projection YOLO detector also involves machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG) methods. Additionally, the paper addresses the challenges of lack of annotated training data and severe geometric distortions, which are common issues in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
